---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
    title="LSCSS Migration"
    description="Migrating existing projects toward Layered Semantic CSS."
>
    <main class="page-shell">
        <section class="site-hero">
            <p class="eyebrow">Migration</p>

            <h1>
                Migrating existing CSS
            </h1>

            <p class="intro">
                LSCSS is designed to support gradual migration rather than full
                rewrites.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="content-block">
            <h2>
                Recommended migration path
            </h2>

            <ol>
                <li>introduce cascade layers</li>
                <li>contain legacy CSS</li>
                <li>split new components into partials</li>
                <li>reduce selector depth</li>
                <li>introduce semantic component naming</li>
                <li>remove unnecessary specificity</li>
                <li>delete legacy code over time</li>
            </ol>
        </section>

        <section class="content-block">
            <h2>
                Legacy layer
            </h2>

<pre><code>@layer legacy, settings, base, utilities,
layout, components, theme, hacks;</code></pre>

            <p>
                Existing CSS can temporarily live inside the legacy layer while
                the rest of the architecture improves around it.
            </p>
        </section>
    </main>
</BaseLayout>
